{center}
{subhead}Rework of the AmigaOne firmware{def}
{left}
{pp}
10.3.2003
{pp}
Hyperion is pleased to announce that it has completed an extensive rework of the 
AmigaOne firmware adding substantial functionality and flexibility for end-users, 
developers and technicians. The new firmware will be incorporated in the A1-XE 
boards which will be shipping shortly.
{pp}
Newly implemented functionality includes:
{pp}
- Migration from PPCBoot 1.16 to U-Boot (PPCBoot 2.0){p}
- Support for PPC 750 FX, MPC 7440/41, MPC 7450/1 CPU's{p}
- Comprehensive GUI for Articia S register configuration{p}
- Comprehensive GUI for general firmware configuration{p}
- Support of additional types of memory modules{p}
- Integration of diagnostic code{p}
- Support for POST card displays allowing for rapid detection of specific hardware faults{p}
- New Articia S start-up code allowing for usage of two banks of unregistered SDRAM{p}
- Booting from Symbios/LSI Logic 53c8xx based SCSI controllers
{pp}
